        "answer_count": 6,
        "title": "Is there a way to simplify/improve this if else?",
        "body": "<p>Newbie here, using Java 11 and trying to figure out if there is a better way to write the below code:<\/p>\n<pre><code>if(code == 1){\n    return (ClassName.static_list1.contains(string_object));\n}else if(code == 2){\n    return (ClassName.static_list2.contains(string_object));\n}else if(code == 3){\n    return (ClassName.static_list3.contains(string_object));\n}else if(code == 4){\n    return (ClassName.static_list4.contains(string_object));\n}else{\n    return false;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>The method returns a boolean value and those lists are coming from a constant class. Please let me know if it can be improved in anyway.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 77773416,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "if-statement",
            "java-11"
        ],
